<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2015/06/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <id>px-proxy</id>
    <version>0.10.3</version>
    <packageSourceUrl>https://github.com/mu88/chocolatey-packages/tree/main/_auto/px-proxy</packageSourceUrl>
    <title>Px Proxy</title>
    <owners>mu88</owners>
    <authors>genotrance</authors>
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/genotrance/px</projectUrl>
    <icon>px-proxy.png</icon>
    <iconUrl>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mu88/chocolatey-packages/main/_auto/px-proxy/px-proxy.png</iconUrl>
    <licenseUrl>https://github.com/genotrance/px/blob/master/LICENSE.txt</licenseUrl>
    <docsUrl>https://github.com/genotrance/px/blob/master/docs/configuration.md</docsUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <tags>proxy http https pac ntlm command-line</tags>
    <summary>Px is a local proxy server to authenticate through an NTLM proxy.</summary>
    <description>Installs Px Proxy from the official GitHub release and exposes the px command through a Chocolatey shim.

Package parameters:
- /SystemWide: Installs files into Program Files instead of the Chocolatey tools location.
- /Startup: Creates one scheduled task to launch Px automatically at system startup.

Px can also be configured via environment variables, see the official Px configuration documentation. For startup tasks running as SYSTEM, machine-level configuration should be used.</description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/genotrance/px/releases</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="px-proxy.png" target="" />
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
  </files>
</package>
